<subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-mean-grouped" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Mean (Grouped)</title>
    <objectives component="outcomes">
        <introduction xml:id="auto_82zx2py4">
            <dl>
                <li xml:id="auto_vdqe0imq">
                    <title>Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_8d0zxdid">
                        3.0 Statistics and Probability
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_nwc7uqre">
                    <title>Sub-Strand</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_fkh0i8bq">
                        3.1 Statistics 1
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_cdm68zrz">
                    <title>Specific Learning Outcomes</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_z2lvv9yp">
                        Determine mean, mode and median of grouped and ungrouped data
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_k5gk4oqp" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Grade Level</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_7t1mqkan">
                        10
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_e7te70f3" component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Estimated Duration</title>
                    <p xml:id="auto_pd9stii1">
                        40 minutes
                    </p>
                </li>
            </dl>
            <p xml:id="auto_o9t003gc" component="lesson-plan">
                <p xml:id="auto_f1ai8fz0"> Upon completion of this lesson, learners will be able to:
                <ol>
                    <li xml:id="auto_kuhepy0d">
                        <p xml:id="auto_ji3gh291">
                            <alert>Know (Conceptual Understanding):</alert> Understand that the mean of grouped data uses midpoints to estimate the average, and that the result is an estimate, not an exact value.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_xtwh0lb4">
                        <p xml:id="auto_1pe7nopn">
                            <alert>Do (Procedural Skill):</alert> Calculate the mean of grouped data using the formula x̄ = Σfx / Σf with midpoints.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_p83vvv83">
                        <p xml:id="auto_ser47k01">
                            <alert>Apply (Application/Problem-Solving):</alert> Apply the grouped data mean formula to real-world datasets and interpret the result.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
                </p>
            </p>
        </introduction>
    </objectives>
    <axiom component="resources">
        <!-- Link to blurb -->
        <xi:include href="../../resources-blurb-lesson.ptx" />

        <sbsgroup widths="45% 45%" margins="2% 2%">
            <sidebyside>
                <p xml:id="auto_xmkwbtyn">
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/statistics-and-probability/statistics-1/mean-grouped.pdf"> Lesson Plan </dataurl>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_7zaueztv">
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/statistics-and-probability/statistics-1/step-by-step-guide_mean-grouped.pdf"> Step-by-Step Guide </dataurl>
                </p>
            </sidebyside>
        </sbsgroup>
    </axiom>

    <xi:include href="../../resources-materials.ptx" />

    
    <introduction xml:id="auto_fscqd7kc">
        <p xml:id="auto_hto6jeyy">
            Grouped data is data that has been organized into classes or intervals together with their frequencies. Instead of listing every single value, the observations are arranged into groups to make large data sets easier to analyze.
        </p>
    </introduction>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Problem-Solving and Discovery</title>
        <dl>
            <li xml:id="auto_wjozlmrf">
                <title>Suggested Time</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_7fhvn9my">15 minutes</p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_mf4cixe5">
                <title>Objective</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_55ti0sdl">Students work in groups to calculate the mean of grouped data by discovering the midpoint concept and the formula x̄ = Σfx / Σf.</p>
            </li>
        </dl>
        <paragraphs>
            <title>Discussion Prompts</title>
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_d1nsox92"><p xml:id="auto_qmbetdas">Can we find the exact mean since we don't have individual values?</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_vod2cplm"><p xml:id="auto_gsc9938s">What value can we use to represent all students in the 100–199 range?</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_kdlcboi9"><p xml:id="auto_xz1dsx5e">How do we combine the midpoints with the frequencies?</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_18tu0660"><p xml:id="auto_1xhlisd3">What does the mean tell us about typical pocket money?</p></li>
            </ul>
        </paragraphs>
    </axiom>

    <activity xml:id="auto_d57qefbq">
        <p xml:id="auto_v5lmy7yp">
            <term>Work in groups</term>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_p5voodzv">
            The table below shows the amount of pocket money, in shillings, that parents give to students per week.
        </p>
        <table xml:id="auto_0jzyncq6">
            <title>Pocket Money Distribution</title>
            <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                <row halign="left" header="yes">
                    <cell>Pocket Money (Ksh)</cell>
                    <cell><m>100 - 199</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>200 - 299</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>300 - 399</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>400 - 499</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>500 - 599</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row halign="left" header="yes"> 
                    <cell>Number of students</cell>
                    <cell><m>8</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>15</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>22</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>20</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
        </table>
        <p xml:id="auto_8prm30r2">
            <ol>
                <li xml:id="auto_eepbhv5h">
                    <p xml:id="auto_ebtp243z">
                        Determine the midpoint for each class interval.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_8m5w6cgp">
                    <p xml:id="auto_0jvohczw">
                        Calculate the mean of pocket money given to students per week.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </activity>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Structured Instruction</title>
        <p xml:id="auto_938fxhis">
            <dl>
            <li xml:id="auto_vtuzrnyl">
                <title>Suggested Time</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_vpgqvgyv">10 minutes</p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_rximfyca">
                <title>Objective</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_mv3r1iaz">To formalize the midpoint concept, the grouped data mean formula x̄ = Σfx / Σf, and the step-by-step process for calculation.</p>
            </li>
            </dl>
        </p>
    </axiom>

    <insight xml:id="auto_gcya54qj">
        <p xml:id="auto_cjha61xj">
            <term>Calculating Mean</term>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_o0grcbpz">
            A frequency distribution table can be used to find the mean for grouped data using the formula:
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_rlsga8ss">
            <md>
                <mrow>\overline{x}  = \amp \frac{ \sum fx}{ \sum f} </mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_jew7m52e">
            Where:
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_93wti1a9"><p xml:id="auto_67cxyhqt"><m>x</m> is the <term>Midpoint</term> of the class interval.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_ve2m1bpv"><p xml:id="auto_j9yb386l"><m>\overline{x}</m> is the mean.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_uy5ue7sc"><p xml:id="auto_7s9e68t4"><m>\sum fx</m> is the sum of the products of the midpoint and frequency.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_xnr8jpfe"><p xml:id="auto_axq3vrq6"><m>\sum f</m> is the sum of frequencies (total number of data points).</p></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_tbfajnj6">
            <term>Midpoint</term> is the average of the lower and upper boundaries of a class interval.
            <md>
                <mrow>\text{Midpoint} = \amp \frac{\text{Lower boundary + Upper boundary}}{2}</mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
    </insight>


    <!-- Exercises -->

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Practice and Application</title>
        <p xml:id="auto_saem3u34">
            <dl>
            <li xml:id="auto_qeyy8kfa">
                <title>Suggested Time</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_y73b53ut">15 minutes</p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_vdqr1wlh">
                <title>Objective</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_2gco9xuj">To apply the grouped data mean formula to calculate the estimated mean from frequency distribution tables.</p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_r2l0n323">
                <title>Teacher's Role</title>
                <p xml:id="auto_bqc2hjdw">Work through examples with learners step by step. Circulate during independent practice and provide assistance where needed.</p>
            </li>
            </dl>
        </p>
    </axiom>

    <example xml:id="auto_w0500c06">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_xlnw48zn">
                A company records the monthly salaries (in KES) of <m>50</m> employees in a frequency distribution table below. Calculate the mean salary.
            </p>
            <table xml:id="auto_em9nzgni">
                <title>Employee Salaries</title>
                <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                    <row halign="left" header="yes">
                        <cell>Salary Range(KES)</cell>
                        <cell>Number of Employees</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>20,000 - 29,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>3</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>30,000 - 39,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>40,000 - 49,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>7</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>50,000 - 59,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>60,000 - 69,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>9</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>70,000 - 79,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>6</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>80,000 - 89,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>90,000 - 99,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>3</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>100,000 - 109,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>2</m></cell>
                    </row>
                </tabular>
            </table>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p xml:id="auto_em8cewjm">
                To calculate the mean, we first find the midpoint (<m>x</m>) of each class and multiply it by the frequency (<m>f</m>).
            </p>
            <table xml:id="auto_nnr958uj">
                <title>Mean Calculation Table</title>
                <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                    <row halign="left" header="yes">
                        <cell>Salary Range(KES)</cell>
                        <cell>Midpoint (<m>x</m>)</cell>
                        <cell>Frequency (<m>f</m>)</cell>
                        <cell><m>fx</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>20,000 - 29,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>25,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>3</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>75,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>30,000 - 39,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>35,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>175,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>40,000 - 49,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>45,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>7</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>315,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>50,000 - 59,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>55,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>550,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>60,000 - 69,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>65,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>9</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>585,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>70,000 - 79,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>75,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>6</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>450,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>80,000 - 89,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>85,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>425,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>90,000 - 99,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>95,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>3</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>285,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>100,000 - 109,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>105,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>2</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>210,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><term>Total</term></cell>
                        <cell></cell>
                        <cell><m>\sum f = 50</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>\sum fx = 3,070,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                </tabular>
            </table>
            <p xml:id="auto_agaz2d3k">
                <md>
                    <mrow>\overline{x}  = \amp \frac{ \sum fx}{ \sum f} </mrow>
                    <mrow>=  \amp \frac{ 3,070,000}{ 50}</mrow>
                    <mrow>=  \amp 61,400</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_zkx2ik12">
                Therefore, the mean salary is <m>61,400</m> KES.
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>

    <example xml:id="auto_q4zwhorq">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_fg928f8v">
                The following data shows the number of minutes <m>50</m> students spent studying for a mathematics test.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_5yv7702p">
                <m>68, 34, 52, 41, 77, 29, 63, 55, 46, 72,</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_w39vef6w">
                <m>38, 64, 51, 83, 47, 36, 59, 74, 62, 44,</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_rpnyjs2q">
                <m>57, 69, 31, 48, 66, 53, 39, 71, 42, 60,</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_sxonhsxw">
                <m>75, 58, 37, 49, 65, 54, 32, 70, 45, 61,</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_upnzbnu7">
                <m>56, 43, 33, 78, 67, 35, 73, 40, 50, 76</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_pqu3y09d">
                Find the mean time taken by the students (use a class width of <m>10</m>)
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p xml:id="auto_3f71z3cp">
                Since the class width is <m>10</m>, the classes are
            </p>
            <tabular left="medium" right="medium" bottom="medium" top="medium">
                <row header="yes">
                    <cell>Class</cell>
                    <cell>Frequency (f)</cell>
                    <cell>Midpoint (x)</cell>
                    <cell>fx</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>20-29</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>1</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>24.5</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>24.5</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>30-39</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>9</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>34.5</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>310.5</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>40-49</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>44.5</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>445</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>50-59</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>54.5</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>545</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>60-69</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>64.5</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>645</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>70-79</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>9</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>74.5</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>670.5</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>80-89</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>1</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>84.5</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>84.5</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell></cell>
                    <cell><m>\sum \text{f} = 50</m></cell>
                    <cell><m></m></cell>
                    <cell><m> \sum \text{fx} = 2725</m></cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
            <p xml:id="auto_k9e5o9ho">
                Apply the mean formula
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_sol8t8so">
                <m> \text {Mean} = \frac{\sum fx}{\sum f}</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_v4csrp3b">
                Mean <m> =\frac{2725}{50} = 54.5\; \text{minutes}</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_x9heiftx">
                Therefore every student take an average of <m>54.5</m> minutes to study for a mathematics test.
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>

